The paper proposes a novel solution for classification of left/right hand movement using EEG signals, which involves the use of deep learning techniques such as LSTM networks with attention mechanism. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to analyze brain activity, which further supports the inclusion of the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed solution in human-computer interaction, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of EEG signals, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Biomedical Engineering (cs.BIO) sub-category.
